A class is defined using the `class` keyword followed by a name (usually PascalCase).

```php
<?php
class Car {
    // ...
}

$myCar = new Car();
$anotherCar = new Car();

var_dump($myCar);
?>
```

The `new` keyword creates an instance (object) of the class. Each object is independent.
